Four people have been killed and three others injured in an accident involving two cars in Groblersdal. JOHANNESBURG - Four people have been killed and three others injured in an accident involving two cars, which collided head on along the R33 in Groblersdal, Limpopo. It has not been determined why the cars collided. Limpopo police spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe says: Four people were killed and three injured on Thursday afternoon during a head-on collision which occurred along R33. At the moment the cause of the accident is still unknown, but we re still investigation. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)